OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,F"Within 24 hours our situation had
OL,7,Fchanged", Stephen said. "We were moved
OL,8,Fto a hotel and told the property we
OL,9,Fhad wanted, was going to be ours and
OL,10,Fwas being adapted.
OL,12,F"It is close to the children's school
OL,13,Fand we can start moving forwards with
OL,14,Four lives'.
OL,16,FA Halton Housing spokesperson said:
OL,17,F"Since the change in Mr Murray's
OL,18,Fcircumstances we have continued to
OL,19,Fwork tirelessly alongside other
OL,20,Fagencies to find an alternative home
OL,21,Ffor Mr Murray and his family.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
