OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,FSpeaking last week, Stephen said he'd
OL,7,Ffelt like was getting no support,
OL,8,Fadding: "I had to take my children
OL,9,Faway from the situation they were in
OL,10,Fto give them a better life, but I feel
OL,11,Flike they've gone backwards.
OL,13,F"They're frozen in time because
OL,14,Fthere's so much they should be getting
OL,15,Fbut they're not. There's no light at
OL,16,Fthe end of the tunnel, it's just
OL,17,Fgetting dimmer and dimmer."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
