OL,3,CDad forced to carry disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs to flat will get new home
OL,6,FStephen was concerned his son's health
OL,7,Fwas being affected by the limited
OL,8,Fspace and not being able to use his
OL,9,Fson's specialist wheelchair, leg
OL,10,Fbraces and upright stand in the flat.
OL,12,FMost people with cerebral palsy have
OL,13,Fmobility issues, but regular exercise
OL,14,Fand play are crucial for maintaining
OL,15,Fand improving their physical strength.
OL,17,FStephen said: "The physio said it's
OL,18,Fgetting worse and it could get to a
OL,19,Fpoint where he won't be able to
OL,20,Fstretch his legs out.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
